Class DoubleLinkedCircularList

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.DoubleLinkedCircularList

  • public class DoubleLinkedCircularList
extends java.lang.Object
    a doubly linked list with a sentinel in between the last and first item. created specifically to hold Fibonacci Heap nodes. 
     Runtime complexity:
 insert is O(1)
 search is O(N)
 delete if given node is O(1), else O(N)
    Author:
    nichole

      • insert

        public HeapNode insert(HeapNode node)
        insert new key into circular doubly linked list, runtime is O(1), Example: sentinel -> 2nd inserted -> 1st inserted -> [ sentinel.right ] sentinel <- 2nd inserted <- 1st inserted <- [ sentinel.right ] 
         subsequent traversal by FIFO should use :
    sentinel and proceed left n=number of items
 
 subsequent traversal by LIFO should use :
    sentinel and proceed right n=number of times
 
 runtime complexity is O(1).
        Parameters:
        node -
        Returns:
        inserted child node instance

      • insertAfter

        public void insertAfter(HeapNode existingNode,
                        HeapNode insertNode)
        insert insertNode to a place after existingNode. The method does not preserve left right relationships of insertNode, but preserves those of existingNode. It expects that existingNode is part of this instance's members and updates the number of items, for later use in traversals. 
         Internally the insertNode is to the left of existingNode using the 
 convention of this class.
 
 subsequent traversal by FIFO should use :
    sentinel and proceed left n=number of items
 
 subsequent traversal by LIFO should use :
    sentinel and proceed right n=number of times
 
 runtime complexity is O(1).
        Parameters:
        existingNode -
        insertNode -
